Employee is eligible for health insurance. Employee will receive a notification through HR Links to identify selection of a healthcare provider and enroll into FEHB. There is a 60 day deadline from the appointment date. If an employee fails to enroll, they must wait until open season or have a qualifying life-event to make changes. If you have any questions please contact Benefits & Retirement Center at cpc.benefits-retirement@gsa.gov.

Employee is automatically covered under basic life insurance. Employee must return the SF-2817 form back to the employment office There is a deadline of 60 days from the appointment date to identify selection of basic coverage, additional optional coverage or to cancel coverage, at which time employee must wait until an open season, opt to pay for physical or have a qualifying life-event to make increasing changes. Employee can decrease coverage at any time

Employee is eligible for the FEDVIP if you are in a position that allows you to enroll in the FEHB Program. As a newly hired or newly eligible employee, there is a deadline of 60 calendar days from the appointment date or become eligible to enroll in a FEDVIP dental plan and/or a FEDVIP vision plan. You DO NOT have to wait for your FEHB coverage to become effective before enrolling in the FEDVIP Program. You can obtain information about FEDVIP plans and enroll by visiting the BENEFEDS website at www.BENEFEDS.com or by calling 1-877-888-3337

Employee is automatically enrolled in the Thrifts Savings Plan program with a deduction of 5% of your salary per pay period. To make changes to this percentage to have a money amount deducted; or stop your deductions you will be required to submit a TSP-1 form. During your first 90 days you also have the option of requesting a refund of the automatic 5% if you choose to not participate in the TSP program at this time. See your TSP Welcome letter or contact your HR office.
